HEADWORD: Bordure
<hw>Bor"dure</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>bordure</ets>. See <er>Border</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>A border one fifth the width of the shield,
surrounding the field. It is usually plain, but may be
charged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

